ciscoUspMIB.name: ciscoUspMIB

revisions.description: First version of this MIB module.

ciscoUspMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-cusp@cisco.com
ciscoUspMIB.description: The MIB Module for the management of the Cisco Unified SIP Proxy (CUSP) service. CUSP is a Session Initiation Protocol (SIP) proxy server that helps enterprises aggregate their SIP elements into a centralized architecture in order to simplify and improve the flexibility of their network. MIB has OID's to monitor CUSP specific info like Server Group, Calls Per Second (CPS), Total Calls, Failed Calls, Dropped Calls, License, Up time CPU and Memory info and also traps on Server group elements, CPU and Memory threshold exceed, License exceed, Back up , process going down, Extensive logging and connection.

cuspSystemStateAlert.name: cuspSystemStateAlert
cuspSystemStateAlert.description: This notification is generated when the CUSP system goes up/down. This notification can be enabled/disabled by setting cuspSystemStateAlertEnable.

cuspServerGroupElementAlert.name: cuspServerGroupElementAlert
cuspServerGroupElementAlert.description: This notification is generated when server group element status changes. This notification can be enabled/disabled by setting cuspServerGroupElementAlertEnable.

cuspServerGroupAlert.name: cuspServerGroupAlert
cuspServerGroupAlert.description: This notification is generated when all the elements in the server group goes down or when any one element in the server group comes up after all the elements in the group were down. This notification can be enabled/disabled by setting cuspServerGroupAlertEnable.

cuspMemoryThresholdAlert.name: cuspMemoryThresholdAlert
cuspMemoryThresholdAlert.description: This notification is generated when CUSP memory usage exceeds the cuspMemoryThresholdValue. This notification can be enabled/disabled by setting cuspMemoryThresholdAlertEnable.

cuspLicenseExceededAlert.name: cuspLicenseExceededAlert
cuspLicenseExceededAlert.description: This notification is generated when average CPS exceeds cuspLicenseLimit. This notification can be enabled/disabled by setting cuspLicenseExceededAlertEnable.

cuspLicenseStateAlert.name: cuspLicenseStateAlert
cuspLicenseStateAlert.description: This notification is generated when CUSP license state changes. This notification can be enabled/disabled by setting cuspLicenseStateAlertEnable.

cuspExtensiveLoggingAlert.name: cuspExtensiveLoggingAlert
cuspExtensiveLoggingAlert.description: This notification is generated when extensive debug level logging is enabled in CUSP. Extensive logging might impact the performance and system stability. This notification can be enabled/disabled by setting cuspExtensiveLoggingAlertEnable.

cuspDiskSpaceThresholdAlert.name: cuspDiskSpaceThresholdAlert
cuspDiskSpaceThresholdAlert.description: This notification is generated when the CUSP Disk usage exceeds the cuspDiskSpaceThresholdValue. This notification can be enabled/disabled by setting cuspDiskSpaceThresholdAlertEnable.

cuspBackupProcessFailAlert.name: cuspBackupProcessFailAlert
cuspBackupProcessFailAlert.description: This notification is generated when back up process fails. This notification can be enabled/disabled by setting cuspBackupProcessFailAlertEnable.

cuspConnectionExceptionAlert.name: cuspConnectionExceptionAlert
cuspConnectionExceptionAlert.description: This notification is generated when a connection exception occurs. This notification can be enabled/disabled by setting cuspConnectionExceptionAlertEnable.

ciscoUspMIBModuleCompliance.name: ciscoUspMIBModuleCompliance
ciscoUspMIBModuleCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the Cisco USP MIB.

ciscoUspMIBMainObjectGroup.name: ciscoUspMIBMainObjectGroup
ciscoUspMIBMainObjectGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information on CUSP system parameters.

ciscoUspMIBNotifyGroup.name: ciscoUspMIBNotifyGroup
ciscoUspMIBNotifyGroup.description: A collection of notifications that are generated by the CUSP.

cuspLastCounterResetTime.name: cuspLastCounterResetTime
cuspLastCounterResetTime.description: This object gives the time stamp in date and time when the call counter was last reset. All counters related to calls, CPS and messages would be reset when counter is reset.

cuspSystemState.name: cuspSystemState
cuspSystemState.description: This object gives the CUSP system state. 'up' - System is up. 'down' - System is either offline or going down.

cuspSystemUpTime.name: cuspSystemUpTime
cuspSystemUpTime.description: This object gives the CUSP system up time information.

cuspLicenseLimit.name: cuspLicenseLimit
cuspLicenseLimit.description: This object gives the maximum licensed CPS limit value. Calls will be rejected if the license limit is exceeded.

cuspLicenseState.name: cuspLicenseState
cuspLicenseState.description: This object gives the current license state of the CUSP. 'waiting' - The initial state after an entitlement request while waiting for the authorization request response. 'overage' - The entitlement is in overage. 'outofcompliance' - Requested entitlement is more than the available count. All calls will be rejected. 'notapplicable' - Enforcement mode is not applicable. 'invalidtag' - The entitlement tag is invalid. 'invalid' - Error condition state. 'init' - The initial state after the instance is created but before the entitlement is requested with. 'incompliance' - License registration and entitlement succeeded. 'evalexpired' - Evaluation period has expired. 'eval' - CUSP is using the evaluation period for this entitlement. 'disabled' - Smart Licensing has been deactivated or disabled. 'authorizedperiodexpired' - The authorized period has expired.

cuspSmartAgentState.name: cuspSmartAgentState
cuspSmartAgentState.description: This object gives the current license state of the Smart License Agent. 'unconfigured' - Smart licensing agent is not enabled and and all calls will be rejected in this state. 'unidentified' - Smart licensing is enabled and entitlement information is sent to the agent. Calls will be allowed in this state. 'evalexpired' - Smart agent will move to this state when evaluation period expires. All calls will be rejected in this state. 'transient' - Smart agent is in transient state. 'registered' - CUSP registered with the cloud server but license not yet authorized. 'outofcompliance' - Requested entitlement is more than the available count. All calls will be rejected. 'authorized' - License registration and entitlement succeeded. 'authorizationexpiry' - Renew request failed for more than 90 days. All calls will be rejected.

cuspConfiguredMemory.name: cuspConfiguredMemory
cuspConfiguredMemory.description: This object gives the total memory (RAM) in MB(MegaByte) configured on CUSP.

cuspMemoryUsed.name: cuspMemoryUsed
cuspMemoryUsed.description: This object gives the CUSP current memory (RAM) usage information in MB (MegaByte).

cuspDiskSpaceUsed.name: cuspDiskSpaceUsed
cuspDiskSpaceUsed.description: This object gives the current disk utilization of CUSP in MB (Mega Byte).

cuspTotalCalls.name: cuspTotalCalls
cuspTotalCalls.description: This object gives the total number of calls since the last counter reset.

cuspTotalFailedCalls.name: cuspTotalFailedCalls
cuspTotalFailedCalls.description: This object gives the total number of failed calls since last counter reset.

cuspCPS.name: cuspCPS
cuspCPS.description: This object gives the current running Calls Per Second (CPS) information.

cuspAvgCPSOneMin.name: cuspAvgCPSOneMin
cuspAvgCPSOneMin.description: This object gives the average CPS (Calls Per Second) in the last one minute.

cuspMaxCPSOneMin.name: cuspMaxCPSOneMin
cuspMaxCPSOneMin.description: This object gives the Maximum value of CPS (Calls Per Second) in the last one minute.

cuspDroppedCallsOneSec.name: cuspDroppedCallsOneSec
cuspDroppedCallsOneSec.description: This object gives the count on number of calls dropped in the last one second.

cuspAvgDroppedCPSOneMin.name: cuspAvgDroppedCPSOneMin
cuspAvgDroppedCPSOneMin.description: This object gives the average of 'dropped calls per second' in the last one minute.

cuspMaxDroppedCPSOneMin.name: cuspMaxDroppedCPSOneMin
cuspMaxDroppedCPSOneMin.description: This object gives the Maximum of 'dropped calls per second' in the last one minute.

cuspCallsRoutedOneSec.name: cuspCallsRoutedOneSec
cuspCallsRoutedOneSec.description: This object gives the number of calls routed through CUSP in last one second.

cuspAvgCallsRoutedOneMin.name: cuspAvgCallsRoutedOneMin
cuspAvgCallsRoutedOneMin.description: This object gives the average of 'calls routed per second' in last one minute.

cuspMaxCallsRoutedOneMin.name: cuspMaxCallsRoutedOneMin
cuspMaxCallsRoutedOneMin.description: This object gives the maximum of 'calls routed per second' in the last one minute.

cuspCallsDroppedExceedingLicense.name: cuspCallsDroppedExceedingLicense
cuspCallsDroppedExceedingLicense.description: This object gives the total calls dropped due to exceeding license limit.

cuspStrayMessageCount.name: cuspStrayMessageCount
cuspStrayMessageCount.description: This object gives the number of stray messages information. Stray messages are messages for which CUSP doesn't have a transaction.

cuspNoOfMessagesRecieved.name: cuspNoOfMessagesRecieved
cuspNoOfMessagesRecieved.description: This object gives the total number of messages received.

cuspDiskSpaceThresholdValue.name: cuspDiskSpaceThresholdValue
cuspDiskSpaceThresholdValue.description: The percentage threshold value configured by the user. If the percentage disk space utilization exceeds this limit then cuspDiskSpaceThresholdAlert notification is sent.

cuspMemoryThresholdValue.name: cuspMemoryThresholdValue
cuspMemoryThresholdValue.description: The percentage threshold value configured by the user. If the percentage memory utilization exceeds this limit then cuspMemoryThresholdAlert notification is sent.

cuspServerGroupTable.name: cuspServerGroupTable
cuspServerGroupTable.description: A list of Server Groups. Server groups define the elements with which the Cisco Unified SIP Proxy system interacts for each network.

cuspServerGroupEntry.name: cuspServerGroupEntry
cuspServerGroupEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the ServerGroup Table.

cuspServerGroupIndex.name: cuspServerGroupIndex
cuspServerGroupIndex.description: A unique value, greater than zero, for each server group.

cuspServerGroupName.name: cuspServerGroupName
cuspServerGroupName.description: This object gives the name of the server group.

cuspServerGroupNetwork.name: cuspServerGroupNetwork
cuspServerGroupNetwork.description: This object gives the network name to which the server group belongs.

cuspServerGroupStatus.name: cuspServerGroupStatus
cuspServerGroupStatus.description: This object gives the Server group status as up/partialdown/down. up - All the elements in the server group are up. partialdown - At least one element in the server group is down. down - All the elements in the server group are down.

cuspServerGroupPingStatus.name: cuspServerGroupPingStatus
cuspServerGroupPingStatus.description: This object gives server group ping status. true - Ping is enabled. false - Ping is disabled.

cuspServerGroupLBType.name: cuspServerGroupLBType
cuspServerGroupLBType.description: This object gives the load balancing algorithm for the server group. global - Uses global load balance algorithm. highestq - Uses highestq algorithm where in CUSP picks the first available element with the higest q-value. requesturi - Hash algorithm is on Request-URI. callid - Hash algorithm is on Call-ID. touri - Hash algorithm is on To URI. weight - Uses weight-based scheme.

cuspElementTable.name: cuspElementTable
cuspElementTable.description: A list of elements in a server group table. Also gives information on status(up/down) of the element, its Q value, weight and transport type.

cuspElementEntry.name: cuspElementEntry
cuspElementEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the cuspElementTable.

cuspElementIndex.name: cuspElementIndex
cuspElementIndex.description: A unique value, greater than zero, for each element.

cuspElementName.name: cuspElementName
cuspElementName.description: This object gives the Server group element ID.

cuspElementStatus.name: cuspElementStatus
cuspElementStatus.description: This object gives the server group element status. 'up' - Server group element is up. 'down' - Server group element is down.

cuspElementQValue.name: cuspElementQValue
cuspElementQValue.description: This object gives the Q value of the server group element. Q value is a real number that specifies the priority of the server group element with respect to others in the server group. Q value range is 0.0 to 1.0.

cuspElementWeight.name: cuspElementWeight
cuspElementWeight.description: This object gives the weight of the server group element. Weight is used for load balancing between server group elements.

cuspElementPort.name: cuspElementPort
cuspElementPort.description: This object gives the port number of the server group element.

cuspElementTransport.name: cuspElementTransport
cuspElementTransport.description: This object gives the transport type of the server group element. Transport type can be udp,tcp or tls.

cuspElementTotalCalls.name: cuspElementTotalCalls
cuspElementTotalCalls.description: This object gives the total routed calls to the server group element.

cuspElementFailedCalls.name: cuspElementFailedCalls
cuspElementFailedCalls.description: This object gives the total failed calls on the server group element.

cuspNotifSeverity.name: cuspNotifSeverity
cuspNotifSeverity.description: The classification on the event severity. 'error' - Significant problem. 'warning' - Not immediately significant. 'informational' - Information only.

cuspNotifDetail.name: cuspNotifDetail
cuspNotifDetail.description: This object gives the detailed information on error encountered.

cuspSystemStateAlertEnable.name: cuspSystemStateAlertEnable
cuspSystemStateAlertEnable.description: This variable controls generation of cuspSystemStateAlert. When this is 'true', generation of Notification is enabled and when this variable is 'false', generation of Notification is disabled.

cuspServerGroupAlertEnable.name: cuspServerGroupAlertEnable
cuspServerGroupAlertEnable.description: This variable controls the generation of cuspServerGroupAlert.

cuspServerGroupElementAlertEnable.name: cuspServerGroupElementAlertEnable
cuspServerGroupElementAlertEnable.description: This variable controls the generation of cuspServerGroupElementAlert

cuspLicenseExceededAlertEnable.name: cuspLicenseExceededAlertEnable
cuspLicenseExceededAlertEnable.description: This variable controls the generation of cuspLicenseExceededAlert.

cuspLicenseStateAlertEnable.name: cuspLicenseStateAlertEnable
cuspLicenseStateAlertEnable.description: This variable controls the generation of cuspLicenseStateAlert.

cuspExtensiveLoggingAlertEnable.name: cuspExtensiveLoggingAlertEnable
cuspExtensiveLoggingAlertEnable.description: This variable controls the generation of cuspExtensiveLoggingAlert.

cuspDiskSpaceThresholdAlertEnable.name: cuspDiskSpaceThresholdAlertEnable
cuspDiskSpaceThresholdAlertEnable.description: This variable controls the generation of cuspDiskSpaceThresholdAlert.

cuspMemoryThresholdAlertEnable.name: cuspMemoryThresholdAlertEnable
cuspMemoryThresholdAlertEnable.description: This variable controls the generation of cuspMemoryThresholdAlert.

cuspBackupProcessFailAlertEnable.name: cuspBackupProcessFailAlertEnable
cuspBackupProcessFailAlertEnable.description: This variable controls the generation of cuspBackupProcessFailAlert notification.

cuspConnectionExceptionAlertEnable.name: cuspConnectionExceptionAlertEnable
cuspConnectionExceptionAlertEnable.description: This variable controls the generation of cuspConnectionExceptionAlert.
